---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`Privacy Policy — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="How ThinkingCats collects, uses, and protects your personal data." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="compliance-main">
			<div class="compliance-inner">

				<a href="/" class="back-link">
					<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"/></svg>
					<span>Back to Home</span>
				</a>

				<div class="page-header">
					<div class="icon-badge icon-badge--indigo">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon--indigo"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
					</div>
					<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
				</div>

				<div class="prose-body">

					<section>
						<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
						<p>At ThinkingCats, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy will inform you as to how we look after your personal data when you visit our website (regardless of where you visit it from) and tell you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>2. The Data We Collect</h2>
						<p>Personal data, or personal information, means any information about an individual from which that person can be identified. We may collect, use, store and transfer different kinds of personal data about you:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Identity Data:</strong> Your display name, email address, and Google profile picture provided at sign-in.</li>
							<li><strong>Contact Data:</strong> Email address used for transactional and support communications.</li>
							<li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, device type, time zone, and access logs.</li>
							<li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> How you interact with the platform — pages visited, features used, post generation counts, and subscription activity.</li>
							<li><strong>User Content:</strong> Avatar images you upload, persona descriptions, niche settings, brand guidelines, and RSS feed URLs you configure ("User Inputs").</li>
							<li><strong>Generated Content:</strong> AI-generated posts, captions, and images produced for your account ("Outputs") are stored in your account and associated with your user ID.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect payment card details directly — billing is handled by our third-party payment processor.</p>
						<div class="callout callout--neutral">
							<strong>Children's Privacy (COPPA):</strong> ThinkingCats is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from anyone under 13. If we learn that we have inadvertently collected data from a child under 13, we will delete that information promptly. Users between 13 and 18 must have parental or guardian consent to use the service.
						</div>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>3. Google Sign-In &amp; OAuth Data</h2>
						<p>ThinkingCats uses Google Sign-In (OAuth 2.0) as its authentication provider. When you sign in with Google, we request only the minimum necessary scopes to create and manage your account:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Email address</strong> — used as your account identifier and for transactional communications.</li>
							<li><strong>Basic profile</strong> — your display name and profile picture, used to personalise your dashboard.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>We do <strong>not</strong> request access to your Google contacts, calendar, Drive, Gmail, or any other Google service beyond basic identity. Data received from Google APIs is used solely to authenticate you and operate your ThinkingCats account. It is never sold, shared with advertisers, or used for any purpose unrelated to providing the service.</p>
						<div class="callout callout--indigo">
							<strong>Google API Services User Data Policy:</strong> ThinkingCats's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs to any other app will adhere to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.
						</div>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
						<p>We will only use your personal data when the law allows us to. Most commonly, we will use your personal data in the following circumstances:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>To authenticate your identity via Google Sign-In and maintain your session.</li>
							<li>To provide the AI digital twin generation services.</li>
							<li>To process your brand descriptions, content briefs, RSS context, and prompts through <strong>Google Gemini API</strong> in order to generate AI content Outputs. This data is transmitted to Google's servers for inference only and is not used by ThinkingCats to train proprietary models. See <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Gemini API Terms</a> for how Google handles API inputs.</li>
							<li>To process payments via our third-party processors.</li>
							<li>To manage our relationship with you.</li>
							<li>To improve our website, products/services, marketing, and customer relationships.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
						<p>We use the following third-party services to operate ThinkingCats:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Google (Firebase Auth):</strong> Handles authentication. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
							<li><strong>Firebase (Google):</strong> Stores account data and generated content securely in the cloud.</li>
							<li><strong>Google Gemini API:</strong> Processes content prompts and brand context to generate AI Outputs. Inputs are sent to Google's servers for inference. ThinkingCats does not store your prompts beyond what is necessary to deliver the service. See <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Gemini API Terms</a>.</li>
							<li><strong>Payment processors:</strong> Handle billing; we do not store card details on our servers.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>6. Data Retention &amp; Deletion</h2>
						<p>We retain your personal data and generated content for as long as your account is active. If you delete your account:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Your profile data and generated Outputs will be deleted from our systems within 30 days.</li>
							<li>Uploaded avatar images and persona configurations will be permanently removed from cloud storage.</li>
							<li>Aggregated, anonymised usage statistics may be retained indefinitely as they cannot be traced back to you.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>To request account deletion, email <a href="mailto:support@thinkingcats.com">support@thinkingcats.com</a>.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>7. Data Security</h2>
						<p>We have put in place appropriate security measures to prevent your personal data from being accidentally lost, used or accessed in an unauthorized way, altered or disclosed. In addition, we limit access to your personal data to those employees, agents, contractors and other third parties who have a business need to know.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>8. Your Legal Rights</h2>
						<p>Under certain circumstances, you have rights under data protection laws in relation to your personal data, including the right to request access, correction, erasure, restriction, transfer, or object to processing.</p>
					</section>

					<section class="footer-note">
						<p>Last updated: March 6, 2026. For any questions regarding this policy, please contact us at support@thinkingcats.com</p>
					</section>

				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.compliance-main {
		padding: 8rem 1.5rem 5rem;
	}
	.compliance-inner {
		max-width: 768px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}
	.back-link {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
		text-decoration: none;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		transition: color 0.15s;
	}
	.back-link:hover { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
	.back-link svg { transition: transform 0.15s; }
	.back-link:hover svg { transform: translateX(-3px); }

	.page-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}
	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 5vw, 2.25rem);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		color: #fff;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.icon-badge {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 40px;
		height: 40px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}
	.icon-badge--indigo { background: rgba(99,102,241,0.1); border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.2); }
	.icon--indigo { color: #818cf8; }

	.prose-body {
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
	}
	.prose-body section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
	.prose-body h2 {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
	}
	.prose-body p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
	.prose-body ul {
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}
	.prose-body strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
	.prose-body a { color: #818cf8; text-decoration: none; }
	.prose-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

	.callout {
		margin-top: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
		line-height: 1.65;
	}
	.callout--neutral { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
	.callout--indigo  { background: rgba(99,102,241,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.2); }
	.callout strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); }
	.callout a { color: #818cf8; }
	.callout a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

	.footer-note {
		padding-top: 2rem;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
		font-size: 12px !important;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3) !important;
	}
</style>
